        "text": "I’ve become very aware of his particularity as a person (as well as his *concern with* particularity as a practitioner-theorist of economic transformation) and, by the same token, of some substantial differences between myself and him. We both are lifelong, associationist-socialist, labour-process, in-and-against post-Fordism organisers; but we have differing visions and, over thirty years, have had differing practical-institutional commitments: we’ve been in different activist bubbles or silos. In closing this chapter I need to say some things deriving from such manifest plurality, in the construction of a college of activist literacy. \n"
